subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Color white. Body length without antennae: male 1.4 mm, females 1.3–1.7 mm (holotype—1.7 mm). Shape of body (
Figs 2–3
) and granulation typical of genus. Usually with 8–10 granules around each pso (
Figs 11–12
).

Antennae distinctly shorter than head (ratio 0.6–0.7). AIIIO consists of 5 conical papillae; 2 sensory rods; 2 spherical, finely granulated sensory clubs, and 5 guard chaetae (
Fig. 8
). Ms on Ant. III located laterally, slightly below AIIIO. Ant. IV with about 14 blunt s-chaetae shorter and slightly thicker than dorsal macrochaetae, a subapical organite and ms located on level of second proximal row of chaetae (
Fig. 8
). Ant. I–III with 9–10, 17–18, 15-16 chaetae respectively. Antennal base well marked.

Head ventrally with 4+4 postlabial chaetae along ventral groove. Pro-, meso- and metathorax without ventral cheatae. VT usually with 6–7+6–7 lateral chaetae, without chaetae at base. Chaetotaxy of Abd. I–VI sternites as in 
Fig. 4
. Trace of reduced furca in shape of small patch of fine granulation with four small dental chaetae posteriorly, arranged in more or less clear row (ma row chaetae); one manubrial row of chaetae, mp-row with 2–3+2–3 chaetae (external ones as macrochaetae) (
Figs 4–5
). Genital plate with 16–20 chaetae in adult females and about 42 chaetae in male. MVO situated near anterior margin of Abd. IV sternite, above trace of reduced furca, consisting of about 28 thick, weakly curved chaetae, located closely together in elliptical integumentary pocket (
Fig. 5
). Anal valves with numerous acuminate chaetae: each lateral valve with a0, 2a1; unpaired anal valve with chaetae a0, 2a1, 2a2, b0, 2b1, 2b2, 2b3, c0, 2c1, 2c2, five or seven of which (b0, b1, b2 and rarely b3) are thickened and curved upwards (
Fig. 7
).

Legs: Subcoxae 1 of I–III legs with 4, 5–6, 5–6 chaetae, subcoxae 2 with 1, 3, 5, coxae with 4, 11, 13–14, trochanters with 11, 11–13, 11–13, femora with 18, 18–20, 18–20, tibiotarsi of legs I–III with 21–22(11+8+2-3), 21–22(11+8+2–3), 20(11+7+2) chaetae, respectively. Claws always with a pair of small lateral teeth and inner tooth (
Fig. 9
). Empodial appendage without basal lamella 0.4–0.5 times as long as inner edge of claw (
Fig. 9
).
